'''Flow marks''', also known as '''flow lines''', are [[mold]]ing [[Product defect|defects]] that can occur in the manufacturing process of [[injection molding]]. They are best described as directionally "off tone" wavy lines or patterns. The reason for this is that the Injection speed is set too slow (the [[plastic]] has cooled down too much during injection, injection speeds must be set as fast as you can get away with at all times).

